b'       Title :  Radiotracer Applications in Industry and Environment                Speaker:  Dr. H.J.Pant Scientific OfficerH & Head, Radiotracer Applications Section Isotope Production and Applications Division Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai400 085 Tel. +912225593854 (Office), +919869740717 (Mobile) Email: hjpant@barc.gov.in, hjpant02@gmail.com  Brief Bio      Dr. Harish Jagat Pant obtained his M.Sc Degree in Physics from H.N.Bahuguna Garhwal University, Srinagar Garhwal in . He joined Isotope Applications Division, Bhabha Atomic Research Centre, Mumbai in 1988 after graduating from the 31 nd  Batch of BARC training school. He obtained his Ph.D degree in Physics from Mumbai University in 2000. He is currently serving as the Head, Radiotracer Applications Section in Isotope Applications Division of Bhabha Atomic Research Centre, Mumbai.     His research interests include development and applications of radioisotope techniques for troubleshooting, measurement of hydrodynamic parameters, process visualization and evaluation of design of chemical process systems in industry. He has developed a number of radiotracer techniques and applied them in various industries in India.  He was awarded DAE Scientific and Technical Excellence Award2010\x08; for his outstanding contribution in the field of Radiotracer Applications in Industry.    He has more than eightyfive publications in international journals and international/national conferences/symposiums.    He is a member of International Atomic Energy Agency\'s expert panel on Industrial Applications of Radioisotopes and was deputed to Thailand, Algeria, Indonesia, Egypt, Republic of Korea and Malaysia as a Technical Cooperation Expert. He is also National Project Coordinator of IAEA/RCA Projects on &q;uot; Diagnosing Industrial Multiphase Systems by Process Visualization using Radiotracers and Sealed Sources".   Venue:  MSB 241  Time:  2:00 PM on Thursday, March 31 2016  Tea @ 1:45 PM (MSB 240)    